1. Baskı
This is My New Homeland  Life Stories of Turkish Jewish Immigrants
https://imageserver.kitapyurdu.com/select.php?imageid=2373285&width=500&isWatermarked=true
2016-11-08
 192,50
This work is a compilation of life stories of twenty Turkish Jews, born and raised in Turkey, and who have settled in new homelands. They now live in the United States, Canada, France, Israel, Switzerland, the United Kingdom, and Australia. Through their stories the reader will be able to have glimpses of their lives before and after leaving Turkey and understand the reasons that pushed them to emigrate.
